<item>
            <title>[SOLR-3899] SolrCore.getNewIndexDir() always print warning</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3899</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;SolrCore.getNewIndexDir() will always log a warning on the first run. The intention of the check was probably to see if the index dir changed between invocations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I provide a SVN patch to solve the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows 7 x64&lt;br/&gt;
JDK 7u7-x64&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
