                            <comment id="13464474" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Thu, 27 Sep 2012 05:54:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the behavior is probably fine? Mostly this is just to inform - a change from null to the first dir seems fine to log if you are going to log subsequent changes. No biggie either way.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This should be info level and not warn IMO though. It&apos;s not a situation that warrants warning about.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13464479" author="tbergman" created="Thu, 27 Sep 2012 06:01:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Changing the log level to info will also be a good solution. What I wanted was to get rid of the unnecessary warning in the log for each core during startup.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
